The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner - Summer season from today
                                                                                                               Summer season from today
            SRIMAX                        
	Bangalore: The 26-day Bangalore summer season begins from Saturday. The racing during the season will be held on Saturdays and Sundays except the last two weeks. The season concludes on August 7.          
	Apart from local trainers, five from Mumbai  Karthik Ganapathy, Pesi Shroff, Nosher Cama, Altamash Ahmed and Dallas Todywalla, three from Hyderabad  Leo DSilva, Vittal Deshmukh and Shehzad Abbas  would be bringing their wards to compete here.          
	The Derby would be sponsored by the UB Group and the club has guaranteed a total stake money of Rs. 1.05 crore for the blue riband event. In all, the season is expected to be an exciting one.          
	On the opening day, trainer B. Prithvirajs ward, Rare And Precious, is fancied to win the Krishnaraja Wadiyar Cup, the feature event. Harish partners the Juniper-Erina son.          
